text: Jelmer Jonker (born 23 September 1993) is a Dutch korfball player. He is a member of PKC and the Netherlands national korfball team. With the national team he won the gold medal at the 2022 World Games in Birmingham, Alabama. ==Achievements== ===Club=== *Korfbal League champion, 2x (2021) * champion, 1x (2019) * champion, 1x (2021) *Goal of the year, 1x (2021) ===National team=== *World Games champion, 1x (2022) *European champion, 2x (2018, 2021) ==References== Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch korfball players
title: Jelmer Jonker
